      "content": "it's just exhausting. pretending to be that person every day—the one who works, and eats, and talks, and exists in the world—it feels like a lie. i'm just a hollow shell carrying around a costume. i don't even know why i'm trying to fight to get back to a version of me that doesn't even exist anymore. it feels more honest to just... stop performing. to just let the window close.",
